Data Cloud Billable Usage Types

Usage of certain Data Cloud features impacts credit consumption. For more information on how usage is billed, refer to your contract or contact your account executive.

Customers whose Data Cloud orgs are operating under a Customer Data Platform license should refer to Customer Data Platform Billable Usage Calculations instead.

Data Service Usage
Service usage calculations are based on records processed, queried, or analyzed. Service usage applies to Data Cloud, Data Cloud for Marketing, and Data Cloud for Tableau customers.

TYPE	DESCRIPTION
Batch Data Pipeline	
Usage is calculated based on the amount of batch data processed by Data Cloud data streams across all connectors.
Data Transforms--Usage is calculated based on the higher of the number of rows read or number of rows written.

Batch Profile Unification	
Usage is calculated based on the number of source profiles processed by an identity resolution ruleset. After the first time a ruleset runs, only new or modified source profiles are counted.

Batch Calculated Insights	Usage is calculated based on the number of records in all underlying objects used in creating the Calculated Insight each time it runs.
Data Queries	

Usage is calculated based on records processed, except for Accelerated Queries and Real-Time Profile API queries.

Unstructured Data Processed	

Usage is calculated based on the amount of unstructured data that is processed. For example, if the search index processes 100 PDF documents that are 1 MB each, usage is calculated as 100 MB.

Streaming Data Pipeline	Usage is calculated based on the number of records ingested by data streams with stream processing and the number of records processed by streaming data transforms.
Streaming Calculated Insights	Usage is calculated based on the number of records processed.
Streaming Actions (including lookups)	Usage is calculated based on the number of records processed.

Real-Time Profile API	Usage is calculated based on records processed.
Inferences	Usage is calculated based on the count of inferences, or outputs, of an AI Model in Einstein Studio.

Data Share Rows Shared (Data Out)	Usage is calculated based on the number of new and changed records that are processed as part of the data share.
Data Federation or Sharing Rows Accessed	

For data federation, usage is calculated based on the number of records returned. For a data share, usage is calculated based on the number of rows returned to fulfill an external data lakeâ€™s request.

Sub-second Real-Time Events & API	

Usage is calculated based on the sum of the number of profile events, engagement events, and API calls processed in the sub-second real-time layer.
Data Storage

Storage refers to the amount of data stored in Data Cloud. Storage used outside of Data Cloud isn't counted toward this limit.

TYPE	DESCRIPTION
Storage Beyond Allocation	Usage is calculated based on the amount of storage used above the amount allocated.
Data Spaces

Data space usage applies to Data Cloud, Data Cloud for Marketing, and Data Cloud for Tableau customers.

TYPE	DESCRIPTION
Data Spaces	Usage is calculated based on the number of data spaces beyond the default data space.

Marketing Feature Service Usage

Service usage calculations for segmentation and activation are based on records of data processed, queried, or analyzed. Service usage applies to Data Cloud for Marketing customers only.

TYPE	DESCRIPTION
Segmentation	Usage is calculated based on the number of records processed.
Batch Activations	Usage is calculated based on the number of records processed.

Ad Audiences Service Usage

Service usage calculations for ad audiences are based on the number of audiences.

TYPE	DESCRIPTION
Ad Audiences	Usage is calculated based on the number of ad audience targets.

Sub-second Real-Time Service Usage

Service usage calculations for real-time service is based on the number of records associated with real-time data graphs.

TYPE	DESCRIPTION
Sub-second Real-Time Profiles & Records	

Usage is calculated based on the maximum number of unique records associated with each real-time data graph at any point during the billing month.
title: Salesforce Data Cloud Billable Usage Types
